I made reservations for Valentine's Day and it turned out to be a disaster.  First, the waitress Veronica was inadvertently rude. What I mean by "inadvertently" is she made comments in regards to the cost of service (minimum $75 per guest + 23% gratuity) not ONCE, not TWICE, but THREE times. It made things very uncomfortable in front of my date. It's as if she didn't believe I could afford a meal from such an establishment. My date was irritated, however we kept our cool and didn't react.  Next, I ordered the same dish (Seafood Pasta) for both me and my date. Unbeknownst to me, Veronica put in an order for just ONE dish. The cook (gentleman dressed in an apron) came to the table and advised us to SHARE the dish and wait for the remaining dish. Mindblowing....I know. Remind you, I'M ON A DATE.  After we finished our delicious meal, we placed 2 more orders for carry out. The wait time for 2 chicken dishes was 1 hour total. No exaggeration....ONE HOUR FOR CHICKEN. It's as if the kitchen staff was overwhelmed by a typical holiday crowd.  While leaving I complained to The Manager - Jennifer. She was professional however didn't offer much of a response. I don't usually write reviews. I just couldn't believe how horrific of an experience this was considering it was Valentine's Day. Yes the food was good, however the service was unbearable. I wouldn't recommend restaurant.

I was so surprised by how much I liked my experience at Prosecco! I had had low expectations because it wasn't an Italian restaurant that I had heard much about in Chicago but the food and service totally turned that upside down.  Upon arrival, we were each given a Prosecco toast as we browsed the menu. We got Salsiccia (grilled Italian sausage), Tartufate (orecchiette, cremini, asparagus, sun-dried tomatoes, black truffle cream, Grana Padano, white truffle oil), and a farfalle pasta special that had smoked and fresh salmon. Everything was scrumptious. The sausage had good flavor and wasn't too salty, and the pastas were cooked perfectly al dente. We were surprised by how filling the portions were, both the antipasti and pastas. There was a ton of salmon in the farfalle special, and the Tartufate really hit the truffle-flavor craving I had without being too greasy or creamy.  The décor, lighting, and ambiance lent itself to a luxurious-feeling space, and our waiter was so nice and attentive the entire time. The restaurant was pretty busy but not loud. I'd totally come back for a special event or celebration next time! The only thing that bumped it down a star was that the complimentary bread was quite stale and dry, and the price of the antipasti was more expensive on our bill ($16) than it was on the menu ($13). Price is not the issue here, it was just somewhat of a surprise.

Had an empty glass of wine for 15 minutes before being asked for a refill, ordered lamb and subbed the green beans out with potatoes, and needless to say, they gave me the green beans. waitress said potatoes would be out in a couple of minutes which was true. Problem was they were SCORCHING hot like they cooked them at 800 degrees just to get them out quick. My date ordered the salmon medium and it came out damn near rare. I will say, the lamb was cooked to perfection and delicious but the rest of the experience over shadowed that. There are hundreds of great places to eat in Chicago. Don't make the same mistake we did.

My husband decided to take me for a dinner. We came to celebrate Valentine’s Day, and unfortunately it was the worst dinner ever!!! Let’s start from the beginning, we came on time and everything was ok, we got a table and decided to order drinks, I ordered wine and my husband ordered beer. Our server didn’t know how to pour beer correctly so it was all over the table. Then we ordered an appetizers, I let me server know that I’m pescetarian and I don’t eat meat. I asked him if the clams appetizer has any meat, he said “no”, so I ordered it. After we got our appetizers and I started eating it, I realized that something there looks like pieces of sausages, I asked my server again if it’s meat, he said: “absolutely not! It’s clams or fish” I was like okay, thanks. And I gave it to try to my husband, he said that it is meat!!!! So I told my server once again, he said: “ok, I’m sorry about that, it’s gonna be on a house”. Are you guys serious? First of all, what if had an allergy? I could die because your server doesn’t know what ingredients are in every dish!? Secondly, not eating meat, is my lifestyle, my choice and it’s very important to me! First time in 3 years since I became pescetarian, Prosecco restaurant (“high level restaurant “) forced me to eat that meat! Your apologies are nothing. I was about to start crying. It was a couple seated near us, and they got there pasta with pieces of chicken, but on the menu it was only salmon. They were vegetarian too, so they  weren’t  happy as well. But anyway we ordered 2 pastas, one vegetarian for me, another one with shrimps for my husband. Another server (turned out that she was a co-owner  of the restaurant) brought us 2 pastas, and one was  with meat, instead of the one with ordered with shrimps!!!!! So we explained it to her again, she said that she is sorry and she touched me by the shoulder at least 5 times like I’m her friend or something. Lady, don’t touch people in any way! I’m not your friend and I don’t like it! That’s my intimate personal space! Do you know what’s that!?! So in the end, she brought us one more pasta with shrimps and told us that the third pasta is on a house... The rule of the Valentine’s Day was 75$ minimum charge per person, which is a lot!! You can’t spend 75$, seriously for real it’s a lot to spend, their prices are not so high, you could die of the food coma! And especially if you are not drinking, so that stupid. You guys are saying that you are high level restaurant, and you are asking for minimum charge? Lol. If your costumers will like what you do they will spend even more.... hold on, it’s not the end of the story. We got our check, and they took my clams appetizer out of the bill, but in the end of the check they added it again!!!! Can you imagine??? I was sooooo mad, so I was asking our server to come to our table again, I was like what’s wrong with you guys??? And it was 22% tip included!! Do you really think that’s normal!?!? 22% tips are for really high level of service, your service worth 0%, in any fast food they serve you better then at your “restaurant “. And then..... their fancy chief (second co-owner) came to our table and started screaming on us, tore a check from my hand and started his loud show: “I’m so tired of you, relax, everything is on a house! We are very busy today. And  you ruined everyone’s Valentine’s Day and bla bla bla”.  excuse me sir, don’t you think you ruined our dinner????? And do you really think that I care if you are busy or not? It’s none of my business! It’s so unprofessional to explain why you messed up, I don’t want to hear your excuses, because I DO NOT CARE!!!!! I came to relax, to pay 150$ plus tax and plus 22% tips and not to solve your problems! In the end their manager came to our table, and he was the only one polite and professional there. I will never come again, I will post my review on every social media! I DONT recommend this restaurant to anyone! Please be aware!!!

The decor is very nice, was decorated for Christmas and it felt very warm and comforting. The food was OUTSTANDING! We ordered a half order of the Orecchiette Tartufate, the Filetto Di Manzo and the Saltimbocca Di Vitello. We finished off with the flourless chocolate cake. Our server was Christian--he was phenomenal; very attentive and his wine recommendation was perfect. It was such a nice evening and I will definitely be back!
Excellent food, Excellent service, Excellent atmosphere.  Honestly, what more is there?

I have been here a few years ago but I was young so I don't remember my experience but I just went again a few nights ago with my uncles', not for food, just drinks. The bartender, Kevin? I think, made my friend and I the most amazing drinks ever! If you don't know what you want, give him a good idea of what you like and he can surprise you with an awesome drink!

Overpriced for the portion/complexity of the dishes served. Restaurant Week or not this is a bad way to portray the business. The food sounded alot more complex and calculated on the menu than what arrived at the table. Minimal labored talent imposed on the look and taste of the dishes. Will not be going back.
(Translated by Google) Great service. Excellent menu.  (Original) Ótimo atendimento. Excelente cardápio.

Really liked our evening at Prosecco.  Foremost the service was unfailingly excellent at every contact point at the restaurant - greeter, bartender, waiter and owner.  Everyone treats you with cheerful interest and desire to serve.  The food was very good - our caprese salad was especially good as the waiter suggested a special version with their house-grown heirloom tomatoes combined with a buffalo mozzarella that was to die for - incredibly creamy and rich - topped with a basil infused olive oil.  Mains were very good too.  If you're interested in a romantic evening or a special night (it's justifiably expensive), you will not leave disappointed.
Love this place! Everyone is super nice and the portions and food are terrific! Their avocado shrimp starter is amazing! Love coming here off peak hours. Great spot!

My boyfriend and I went to Prosecco this past Saturday before a movie and we loved it. They give you a glass of champagne on the house as soon as you sit down and this puts you in the mood. This restaurant is very romantic. The food was great. We had 2 appetizers and main dish and we were not full or hungry. We will definitely return.
Superb - Culinary perfection - Outstanding bar and service
This IS the best restaurant in the City of Chicago, hands down.

What a pleasant surprise when my friend chose Prosecco.  I had not heard of it prior to our dinner.  Nice touch with the welcome glass of champaign.  Very attentive server. Nice wine selection...Chianti.  Each course was so good we shared everything.  We were both elated with the food, service and environment.  Price was fair for the value.  They even cleaned up my "adding" error on my Visa the next day with style and class.  I will definitely go back.
The staff here is great and very knowledgeable of the food and drinks. I really like the scallops, the burrata and the pastas.

Maybe it's because my family knows the owner that I'm a bit biased, but I honestly LOVE this restaurant. The food is DIVINE, the service is impeccable and the decor is simply perfect. Although it is a bit pricey, the quality of the food is so great that it is worth the splurge!!!

We visited here last evening, enjoying a wonderful meal and a bottle of wine from their extensive wine list.  To start off, we tried the Polpetti e Calamari Alla Grigliati which was a combination of octopus, calamari and fingerling potatoes.   What a delight!  For a main course we shared the Costoletta di Agnello (Rack of Lamb), finding it to just melt off the bone.  Wrapping up, we enjoyed the Torta di Cioccolato (flourless chocolate cake) and Torta di Mele (Apple Tart).  Needless to say, we left fully satisfied from a terrific meal.  The service was prompt and the decor just perfect, providing a nice casual elegance for a comfortable dining experience.  It's a terrific place for a nice meal!
Awesome spinach gnocchi

One of the most romantic restaurants in the city.  Awesome food and wine selection.  Scallops are my favorite dish and really quite unique.  Service is great and servers are very knowledgable and portion size is reasonable.  Really good specials.

overall, a very good experience! warm, comfortable venetian style decor. we arrived early for our reservations, bartender was very knowledgeable about the extensive italian wine list, he suggested the best options, not most expensive.  he also gave us his recommendations for his favs on the menu. highly recommended, grilled octopus calamari appetizer, tricolor salad and orecchiette with truffles, you will not be sorry!
